@startuml
title Sequence Diagram: Resource Deletion (File & Directory)

actor User
participant "Client (CLI)" as Client
participant "Metadata Server\n(Master)" as Master
participant "Storage Nodes\n(Cluster)" as Nodes

== 1. Client-Side Confirmation ==
User -> Client: Type 'adria rm <path>' or 'adria rmdir <path>'
activate Client
Client --> User: "Warning: this will permanently delete resources. Are you sure? [y/N]"
User -> Client: Input 'y'

== 2. Metadata & Resolution ==
Client -> Master: Request Delete (Path, Auth Token)
activate Master
Master -> Master: Validate Token & Check Ownership/Permissions
Master -> Master: Resolve Path\n(Identify all files and chunks involved)

== 3. Physical Deletion (Cascading) ==
Master -> Nodes: Command: Delete Chunks (List of Chunk IDs)
activate Nodes
note over Nodes: Physically remove\nbinary files from disk
Nodes --> Master: ACK (Chunks Deleted)
deactivate Nodes

== 4. Metadata Cleanup ==
Master -> Master: Remove resource records from SQL Database
Master --> Client: 200 OK (Deletion successful)
deactivate Master

Client --> User: "Resource successfully deleted."
deactivate Client

@enduml
